theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_of_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 A → closure A = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hP3
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `A ⊆ interior (closure A)` implies `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
    have : closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      exact closure_mono hP3
    simpa using this
  · -- Trivially, `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A`, so taking closures preserves inclusion
    have : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
      exact closure_mono interior_subset
    simpa using this

theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P2 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → closure A = closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP2
  have hP1 : Topology.P1 A := Topology.P2_imp_P1 (A := A) hP2
  exact Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1 hP1
